<h1 id="gnome-core-apps-and-libraries">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gnome-core-apps-and-libraries" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GNOME Core Apps and Libraries
</h1>

<h3 id="calendar">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#calendar" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Calendar <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A simple calendar application.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@theevilskeleton:fedora.im">Hari Rana | TheEvilSkeleton (any/all)</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>GNOME Calendar 46 beta was released, bringing some exciting changes and additions:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://fortintam.com/en">Jeff Fortin</a> worked on <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/354">harmonizing the mini calendar&rsquo;s week numbers with GNOME Shell</a>.</li>
<li><a href="https://feaneron.com/">Georges Stavracas</a> ported every window to <a href="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/main/class.Dialog.html"><code>AdwDialog</code></a>, and <a href="https://sungsphinx.codeberg.page/">Dexter Reed</a> ported the about window to <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/411"><code>AdwAboutDialog</code></a>.</li>
<li><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/ramialkawadri">Rami Alkawadri</a> fixed a bug in the creation popover where <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/359">full-day events would show &ldquo;00:00 — 00:00&rdquo;</a>.</li>
<li>Georges Stavracas ported the <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/365">date selector to Settings portal</a>.</li>
<li><a href="https://felipekinoshita.com/">Felipe Kinoshita</a> added <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/380">debug information to the about dialog</a>.</li>
<li>Georges Stavracas ported from <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/402">GtkLabel to GtkInscription for displaying events</a>. Using GtkInscription for this use case increases performance.</li>
<li>Hari Rana added <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/401">month separators</a>, making it easier to distinguish beginning and end of each month.</li>
<li>Hari Rana added a <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/393">lock icon for read-only calendars</a></li>
<li>Hari Rana <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/389">improved the handling of event names</a>, which adds visual feedback to when the event name is invalid.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2024/03/twig-137/5781cb6c4c6a9b317ef58550c264abd8790e34a11761755798108635136.png" alt="" />

